<section class="problem-section" style="max-width: 100%; padding: 80px 40px;">
  <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h2 class="section-title">If You Have Belly Fat, Most Solutions Won't Work</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">
      Here's the scientific reason your gut hangs over your jeans — and why traditional diet & exercise isn't working.
    </p>

    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-image">
        {% assign max_width = section.settings.max_width |  divided_by: 2 %}
        {% assign max_width_px = max_width | append: 'px' %}
        {% if section.settings.image != blank %}
          {{
            section.settings.image
            | image_url: width: max_width
            | image_tag: class: 'w-full', sizes: max_width_px
          }}
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      <div class="problem-content">
        <h3>The Estrogen-Belly Vicious Cycle</h3>
        <p style="color: #666; margin-bottom: 25px;">
          Your belly fat contains an enzyme called <strong>aromatase</strong>. Its job? Convert your testosterone into
          estrogen. More belly fat = more aromatase = more conversion.
        </p>

        <div class="cycle-steps">
          <div class="cycle-step">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Testosterone Drops</h4>
              <p>Muscle fades. Metabolism slows. Energy crashes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cycle-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="cycle-step">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Fat Accumulates</h4>
              <p>Especially around the belly. The stubborn kind.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cycle-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="cycle-step">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Aromatase Increases</h4>
              <p>Converts testosterone → estrogen. Faster and faster.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cycle-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="cycle-step">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h4>Estrogen Rises</h4>
              <p>Signals your body to store MORE fat. Cycle repeats.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 14px;">
          <strong>This is a hormonal trap.</strong> Willpower doesn't break it. Dieting doesn't break it. Even TRT
          doesn't break it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="solutions-fail">
      <h3 style="text-align: center; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px;">
        Why Other Solutions Fail
      </h3>
      <p style="text-align: center; color: #666; font-size: 15px;">The problem isn't production. It's conversion.</p>

      <div class="fail-grid">
        {% for block in section.blocks %}
          {% case block.type %}
            {% when 'row' %}
              <div class="fail-card">
                <div class="icon">
                  {% if block.settings.image != blank %}
                    {{
                      block.settings.image
                      | image_url: width: 60
                      | image_tag: class: 'w-full max-w-[60px] rounded-[50px] h-fit', sizes: '60px'
                    }}
                  {% endif %}
                </div>
                <div>
                  {% if block.settings.heading != blank %}
                    <h4>{{ block.settings.heading }}</h4>
                  {% endif %}
                  {% if block.settings.description != blank %}
                    <p>{{ block.settings.description }}</p>
                  {% endif %}
                </div>
              </div>
          {% endcase %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

